{"title_page": "Jakob Friis-Hansen", "text_new": "{{short description|Danish footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jakob Friis-Hansen\n| fullname = \n| height = 1.86m<ref name=\"wf\">{{Worldfootball.net|jakob-friis-hansen|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1967|3|6}}\n| birth_place = [[Copenhagen]], Denmark<ref name=\"nft\">{{NFT|15997|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1 = 1972\u20131982\n| youthclubs1 = [[Boldklubben 1903|B 1903]]\n| years1 = 1983\u20131987\n| clubs1 = [[Boldklubben 1903|B 1903]]\n| caps1 = 43\n| goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 1987\u20131988\n| clubs2 = [[Lyngby Boldklub|Lyngby]]\n| caps2 = 25\n| goals2 = 4\n| years3 = 1988\u20131989\n| clubs3 = [[Boldklubben 1903|B 1903]]\n| caps3 = 37\n| goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 1989\u20131995\n| clubs4 = [[Lille OSC|Lille]]\n| caps4 = 217\n| goals4 = 4\n| years5 = 1995\u20131996\n| clubs5 = [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]]\n| caps5 = 18\n| goals5 = 2\n| years6 = 1996\u20131997\n| clubs6 = [[Hamburger SV]]\n| caps6 = 16\n| goals6 = 1\n| totalcaps = 366\n| totalgoals = 15\n| nationalyears1 = 1990\u20131996\n| nationalteam1 = [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 19\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1 = 2003\u20132007\n| managerclubs1 = [[Hellerup IK]]\n| manageryears2 = 2007\u20132008\n| managerclubs2 = [[BK Fremad Amager]]\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{fb|DEN}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIFA Confederations Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[1995 King Fahd Cup|1995 Saudi Arabia]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Jakob Friis-Hansen''' (born 6 March 1967) is a Danish former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[defender (association football)|defender]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/1-bundesliga/1996-97/hamburger-sv-12/306/spieler_jakob-friis-hansen.html | title = Friis-Hansen, Jakob | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 2 May 2011}}</ref> At club level, he spent most of his career with French club [[Lille OSC]]. For the [[Denmark national football team|Denmark national team]], he made 19 appearances.\n\nHe is an old friend of former [[England national football team|England]] forward [[Teddy Sheringham]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport-old/football/2008/02/04/teddy-sheringham-s-son-charlie-could-salvage-his-career-in-denmark-115875-20309257/ | title = Teddy Sheringham's son Charlie could salvage his career in Denmark | date= 4 February 2008 | accessdate = 2 May 2011 | publisher = mirror.co.uk}}</ref>\n\nHe was formerly a scout for [[Liverpool F.C.]], and worked as Director of the European Recruitment for [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] between 2011 and 2012.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.dbu.dk/landshold/landsholdsdatabasen/PlayerInfo/982 Danish national team profile] {{in lang|da}}\n* {{Fussballdaten|friishansenjakob}}\n\n{{Denmark squad 1995 King Fahd Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Friis-Hansen, Jakob}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Danish footballers]]\n[[Category:Denmark international footballers]]\n[[Category:Denmark under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Lyngby Boldklub players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Lille OSC players]]\n[[Category:FC Girondins de Bordeaux players]]\n[[Category:Hamburger SV players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:1995 King Fahd Cup players]]\n[[Category:FIFA Confederations Cup-winning players]]\n[[Category:Danish football managers]]\n[[Category:Fremad Amager managers]]\n[[Category:Danish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-footy-de