enter, Baltimore, Maryland, U.S.}}\n|\n|-\n|3\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|3\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Vinnie DeBarros\n|{{abbr|TKO|Technical knockout}}\n|3 (6), {{small|1:59}}\n|Jun 10, 1977\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Hartford Civic Center|Civic Center]], [[Hartford, Connecticut]], U.S.}}\n|\n|-\n|2\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Willie Rodriguez\n|UD\n|6\n|May 14, 1977\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Civic Center, Baltimore, Maryland, U.S.}}\n|\n|-\n|1\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Luis Vega\n|{{abbr|UD|Unanimous decision}}\n|6\n|Feb 5, 1977\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Baltimore Civic Center|Civic Center]], [[Baltimore, Maryland]], U.S.}}\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col}}\n*[[List of welterweight boxing champions]]\n*[[List of light middleweight boxing champions]]\n*[[List of middleweight boxing champions]]\n*[[List of undisputed boxing champions]]\n*[[List of WBA world champions]]\n*[[List of WBC world champions]]\n*[[List of WBO world champions]]\n*[[List of The Ring world champions|List of ''The Ring'' world champions]]\n*[[List of boxing quintuple champions]]\n*[[Sugar Ray Leonard vs. Roberto Dur\u00e1n II]]\n*[[Sugar Ray Leonard vs. Thomas Hearns]]\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*{{Official website|http://sugarrayleonard.com/}}\n*{{Boxrec|id=000269}}\n*[http://boxing-scoop.com/show_boxer.php?boxer_ID=3987 Sugar Ray Leonard's Amateur Boxing Record]\n*[http://manschoolshow.com/blog/2014/3/12/class-53-being-a-champion-with-sugar-ray-leonard Sugar Ray Leonard in-depth interview about alcohol, cocaine, and being a champion]\n\n{{s-start-collapsible|header={{s-sports}} }}\n{{s-text|style=background:#C1D8FF; font-weight: bold;|text=Amateur boxing titles}}\n{{s-before|before=[[James Busceme]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of